hands_on_practices.solution:
Normalize the PMF by enforcing $\sum_{k=0}^3p_X(k)=1$.  Since $p_X(k)=C(k+1)$ for $k=0,1,2,3$,  
$$
\sum_{k=0}^3p_X(k)
=\sum_{k=0}^3C(k+1)
=C\sum_{k=0}^3(k+1)
=C(1+2+3+4)
=10C
\stackrel{!}{=}1
\;\Longrightarrow\;
C=\frac{1}{10}.
$$
Hence
$$
p_X(0)=\frac{1}{10},\;
p_X(1)=\frac{2}{10},\;
p_X(2)=\frac{3}{10},\;
p_X(3)=\frac{4}{10}.
$$
We seek 
$$
P(X\ge2\mid X>0)
=\frac{P(X\ge2\;\wedge\;X>0)}{P(X>0)}
=\frac{P(X\ge2)}{P(X>0)}
=\frac{p_X(2)+p_X(3)}{p_X(1)+p_X(2)+p_X(3)}
=\frac{\tfrac{3}{10}+\tfrac{4}{10}}{\tfrac{2}{10}+\tfrac{3}{10}+\tfrac{4}{10}}
=\frac{\tfrac{7}{10}}{\tfrac{9}{10}}
=\frac{7}{9}.
$$
